 is really super. Price-drop last until stock runs out or until October 1, 2012. So hurry if you want one.</p><p>This is an exclusive promotion to LEB readers in that way that (last time I checked) bluevm.com still had the original prices on their frontpage and the only way you would know that the price is lowered is by ordering one.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><ul><strong>BlueVM 1</strong><p></p><li>RAM: 64/128 MB</li><li>Disk: 10 GB</li><li>Bandwidth: 250 GB</li><li>vCPU(s) 1 @ 2.5Ghz</li><li>Price:&nbsp;$10 /Yr</li><li><strong><a href=\"http://www.bluevm.com/cart.php?gid=11\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></strong></li></ul></td><td><ul><strong>BlueVM 2</strong><p></p><li>RAM: 128/256 MB</li><li>Disk: 20 GB</li><li>Bandwidth: 400 GB</li><li>vCPU(s) 1 @ 2.5Ghz</li><li>Price:&nbsp;$15 /Yr</li><li><strong><a href=\"https://www.bluevm.com/cart.php?gid=12\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></strong></li></ul></td><td><ul><strong>BlueVM 3</strong><p></p><li>RAM: 256/512 MB</li><li>Disk: 40 GB</li><li>Bandwidth: 1 TB</li><li>vCPU(s) 2 @ 2.5Ghz</li><li>Price:&nbsp;$1.99 /Mo</li><li><strong><a href=\"https://www.bluevm.com/cart.php?gid=13\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></strong></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p><span id=\"more-2894\"></span></p><table><tbody><tr><td><ul><strong>BlueVM 4</strong><p></p><li>RAM: 512/1024 MB</li><li>Disk: 60 GB</li><li>Bandwidth: 2 TB</li><li>vCPU(s) 3 @ 2.5Ghz</li><li>Price:&nbsp;$3.50 /Mo</li><li><strong><a href=\"https://www.bluevm.com/cart.php?gid=14\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></strong></li></ul></td><td><ul><strong>BlueVM 5</strong><p></p><li>RAM: 1024/2048 MB</li><li>Disk: 80 GB</li><li>Bandwidth: 3 TB</li><li>vCPU(s) 4 @ 2.5Ghz</li><li>Price:&nbsp;$5.95 /Mo</li><li><strong><a href=\"https://www.bluevm.com/cart.php?gid=15\" target=\"_blank\">Order Link</a></strong></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>1 IPv4 on all Locations and planned IPv6 in ATL and CA within the next 6 months.</p><p>Link to bluevm TOS is <a href=\"https://bluevm.com/tos.php\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>, but in Justin\u2019s word :<em>\u201cAll allowed if it is legal.\u201d</em><br>\nIn short (the FAQ of terms)<br>\n1. Allow IRC = yes<br>\n2. Allow Tor =&nbsp; mid nodes ONLY , <strong>exit no.</strong><br>\n3. Allow Adult? yes</p><p>If you choose California or Atlanta, your vps will be on a 1 Gbps port and 100 Mbps in Illinois or Kansas.</p><p><strong>Test File/IP</strong></p><p>California: <a href=\"http://neon.bluevm.com/100mb.test\">http://neon.bluevm.com/100mb.test</a><br>\nAtlanta: <a href=\"http://sodium.bluevm.com/100mb.test\">http://sodium.bluevm.com/100mb.test</a><br>\nIllinois: <a href=\"http://64.79.106.221/100mb.test\">http://64.79.106.221/100mb.test</a><br>\nKansas: <a href=\"http://69.30.193.58/100mb.test\">http://69.30.193.58/100mb.test</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>BlueVM.Com was registered in May 2011 as BlueVM Communications LLC in Colorado and is managed by a two-man team consisting of Justin and Arsene.</p><p>Payment methods are; Paypal and Google checkout. No refunds at all according to their policy.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fbluevm-10year-64mb-openvz-in-california-atlanta-illinois-kansas%2F&amp;t=BlueVM%20%E2%80%93%20%2410%2Fyear%2064MB%20OpenVZ%20in%20California%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20Illinois%2C%20Kansas\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label dpsp-first\" title=\"Share on Facebook\"><span class=\"dpsp-network-icon\"></span><span class=\"dpsp-network-label-wrapper